[door closes]

01:22.749 --> 01:24.950
[Mumbling]

01:25.019 --> 01:26.818
Guadalcanal.

01:26.887 --> 01:28.920
[Trumpets blowing]

01:28.989 --> 01:31.656
(Skipper)
'Sub chaser 307 calling
squadron command.'

01:31.725 --> 01:32.791
'do you read me?'

01:32.860 --> 01:35.460
'come in, squadron command.
Come in.'

01:35.529 --> 01:37.495
'we are under
heavy enemy attack.'

01:37.564 --> 01:40.132
'await you instructions.'

01:40.200 --> 01:42.568
'bandits at 10 o'clock.
Look out. Hit the deck!'

01:46.039 --> 01:47.606
'phew! That was
a close one.'

01:47.675 --> 01:49.307
you're telling me.

01:49.376 --> 01:52.878
- 'Are you okay, lieutenant?'
- Yeah.

01:52.947 --> 01:55.747
Lieutenant?

01:55.816 --> 01:56.882
Skipper?

02:00.720 --> 02:01.687
[Grunting]

02:03.757 --> 02:06.058
Transmitter's been
knocked out, sir.

02:06.127 --> 02:08.059
We'll have to
convert the receiver.

02:08.127 --> 02:10.262
(Skipper)
'Harris, give me
that radio manual.'

02:15.936 --> 02:19.638
connect remaining circuits
by plugging into..

02:19.706 --> 02:24.609
Radio frequency located at the
right side of the antenna lead.

02:24.678 --> 02:27.912
Ready to convert the radio
into a transmitter, lieutenant.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.247
Aye, aye, sir!

02:29.315 --> 02:31.250
Evans, hold this book.

02:33.187 --> 02:34.586
Give me a
screwdriver, ferguson.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.855
Quick, man,
a screwdriver!

02:45.065 --> 02:46.831
Now give me
the wire cutters.

02:46.900 --> 02:48.167
Wire cutters!

02:55.409 --> 02:57.242
Ready to transmit, sir.

03:00.514 --> 03:03.148
Dive-bombers at
12 o'clock. Jump, men!

03:03.217 --> 03:04.950
- Aye, aye, sir.
- Run for your lives.

03:22.369 --> 03:23.936
[Snoring]

03:26.506 --> 03:28.207
[Blowing raspberry]

03:29.409 --> 03:30.775
Gilligan.

03:30.844 --> 03:32.444
You're soaking wet.

03:32.513 --> 03:35.013
I know, the lagoon's
full of water.

03:35.082 --> 03:36.815
What were you
doing in the lagoon?

03:36.884 --> 03:39.384
You pushed me overboard when
the dive-bombers came at us.

03:39.453 --> 03:41.787
- What dive-bombers?
- The one you're dreamin' about.

03:41.855 --> 03:44.322
I'd just given you
some tools to fix the radio.

03:44.390 --> 03:45.691
- Tools?
- Yeah.

03:45.759 --> 03:48.359
This screwdriver
and these pair of wire cutters.

03:48.428 --> 03:50.362
'Boy, a near
nightmare out there.'

03:50.430 --> 03:53.365
gilligan, I have not been
out of this hammock.

03:53.434 --> 03:54.866
'You've been walking
in your sleep.'

03:54.935 --> 03:56.234
I have?

03:56.303 --> 03:59.271
Certainly. When you fell
in the water, it woke you up.

03:59.339 --> 04:00.572
Is that what happened?

04:00.641 --> 04:02.941
I could've sworn it was
the other way around.

04:03.010 --> 04:05.710
I'm afraid not. Why
don't you go back to sleep

04:05.778 --> 04:07.913
and no more dive-bombers
tonight, huh?

04:07.982 --> 04:10.281
- Yes, sir.
- Oh, gilligan.

04:10.350 --> 04:12.083
You better wipe those
wire cutters off

04:12.151 --> 04:14.286
before they get rusty.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.896
[Theme music]

04:27.201 --> 04:29.734
(Woman on radio)
'This is Alice mcneal
signing off'

04:29.803 --> 04:33.104
'as I start the last leg of
my round the world flight.'

04:33.172 --> 04:38.109
'open up that golden gate 'cause
San Francisco, here I come.'

04:38.178 --> 04:39.811
[birds squawking]

04:40.914 --> 04:43.715
Professor, according
to my new calculations

04:43.784 --> 04:45.750
she should be passing
right over our island.

04:45.819 --> 04:48.052
There must be some way
we can contact her.

04:48.121 --> 04:50.488
But how?

04:50.557 --> 04:54.058
I got it. I've got it! What we
need is a big roaring fire.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.460
(Professor)
'Yes.'

04:57.631 --> 05:00.164
a big roaring fire
on a hot day like this?

05:00.233 --> 05:02.233
A signal fire, gilligan.
There's a very good chance

05:02.302 --> 05:05.436
that woman flyer will pass
right over this island.

05:05.505 --> 05:08.106
Skipper, we're saved.
We're saved.

05:08.175 --> 05:09.841
We're not saved
yet, gilligan.

05:09.910 --> 05:12.410
We've gotta figure out some way
to attract her attention.

05:12.479 --> 05:15.347
I'll take off my shirt,
jump, and yell and wave it.

05:15.415 --> 05:17.915
Gilligan, she's gonna be
passing over at 5000 ft.

05:17.984 --> 05:20.118
How do you suppose
she'll see you?

05:20.187 --> 05:21.953
I'll stand
on your shoulders.

05:22.021 --> 05:24.089
That's good, gilligan.
That's very good.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.891
I've got an even better idea,
skipper. An even better idea.

05:26.960 --> 05:29.594
- We'll build a human tower.
- Human tower?

05:29.663 --> 05:30.895
You'll be on the bottom

05:30.964 --> 05:32.631
professor stands
on your shoulders

05:32.699 --> 05:34.899
Mr. howell stands on his,
i stand on Mr. howell's--

05:34.968 --> 05:36.534
Mrs. howell stands
on your shoulders

05:36.603 --> 05:37.802
ginger stands
on her shoulders

05:37.871 --> 05:39.837
and we'll have Mary Ann
at the top.

05:39.906 --> 05:42.274
No, I think ginger
ought to be at the top.

05:42.342 --> 05:43.507
Why?

05:43.576 --> 05:45.510
Because she's wearing
high heels.

05:45.579 --> 05:47.812
I think a signal fire's
our best bet, gilligan.

05:47.881 --> 05:51.015
But I don't know if she can see
through that nimbus cumuli.

05:51.084 --> 05:54.452
Yeah, and all those clouds
are in the way too.

05:54.521 --> 05:56.388
We better do
something pretty quick.

05:56.456 --> 05:58.623
No telling how soon
she might pass over.

05:58.691 --> 06:01.426
If only I could remember how
you fixed the radio last night.

06:01.495 --> 06:02.660
What radio?

06:02.729 --> 06:05.029
The one in the sub chaser
in my nightmare.

06:05.098 --> 06:07.965
We were under enemy attack and
the transmitter knocked out.

06:08.034 --> 06:09.434
Sub chaser?

06:09.503 --> 06:12.036
Enemy attack? The transmitter
got knocked out?

06:12.105 --> 06:13.939
Don't you remember?
I told you last night.

06:14.007 --> 06:16.107
I thought he was walking
in his sleep.

06:16.176 --> 06:18.210
Turned out he was
walking in my sleep.

06:18.278 --> 06:19.844
What else happened?

06:19.913 --> 06:22.147
I don't know.
Whole thing's kinda hazy today.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.349
The whole nightmare
seems like a dream.

06:24.418 --> 06:26.217
Gilligan.

06:26.285 --> 06:28.853
Gilligan, little buddy.
You said I fixed the radio.

06:28.922 --> 06:29.854
How did I do it?

06:29.923 --> 06:32.524
You turned it
into a transmitter.

06:32.592 --> 06:35.059
I remember. It happened
at guadalcanal.

06:35.128 --> 06:37.362
No, it happened
over there by the lagoon.

06:37.431 --> 06:39.564
We were about
a mile off shore.

06:39.633 --> 06:42.600
The transmitter got hit. We were
strafed by enemy fighters.

06:42.669 --> 06:43.935
I had to do
something fast.

06:44.004 --> 06:46.004
Skipper, let me tell it.
It was my dream.

06:46.073 --> 06:48.840
Is it possible to convert
a radio into a transmitter?

06:48.908 --> 06:51.976
Sure! All you need a screwdriver
and a pair of wire cutters.

06:52.045 --> 06:54.378
Got 'em right here, sir.

06:54.447 --> 06:55.913
It's a simple procedure.

06:55.982 --> 06:59.584
It's just a matter of
reversing the circuits by..

06:59.653 --> 07:02.053
- Gilligan, how did I do it?
- I don't know.

07:02.122 --> 07:03.888
But you must have
seen something.

07:03.957 --> 07:05.524
I didn't even see
the dive-bombers.

07:05.592 --> 07:07.893
Next thing I knew
i was swimming for my life.

07:07.961 --> 07:09.694
Think, skipper.
Come on, think.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.897
How did you convert
that radio?

07:13.266 --> 07:14.732
I don't remember.

07:14.801 --> 07:17.601
I know. I'll go back to sleep
and get on the boat

07:17.670 --> 07:18.870
a little earlier
this time.

07:18.939 --> 07:20.938
That was my dream
last night, not yours.

07:21.007 --> 07:23.041
- But you told--
- 'i know what I told you.'

07:23.110 --> 07:26.211
but I was wrong. Looks like
i owe you an apology.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.479
Forget it, skipper. If you
hadn't pushed me overboard

07:28.548 --> 07:30.182
I would have been
blown to bits.

07:31.951 --> 07:35.287
It has something to do with
the main coil. A main coil.

07:35.355 --> 07:36.988
- Main coil.
- Main coil.

07:38.258 --> 07:40.425
It's no use.

07:40.493 --> 07:42.893
I can't sleep
with somebody watching.

07:42.962 --> 07:44.929
Alright, skipper.
You try it on your own.

07:44.998 --> 07:48.232
Yeah. Concentrate on getting to
sleep. Leave the worrying to us.

07:48.301 --> 07:51.068
The only thing you gotta worry
about is getting to sleep.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.170
Thanks, gilligan.

07:52.239 --> 07:53.872
You got seven lives
depending on you.

07:53.941 --> 07:55.707
'That's a big
responsibility for one man.'

07:55.776 --> 07:57.776
'unless you sleep,
you won't walk in your sleep'

07:57.844 --> 07:59.844
and we can't change the
radio into the transmitter.

07:59.913 --> 08:03.482
- So relax and go to sleep.
- Let's go, gilligan.

08:04.951 --> 08:08.286
You don't have to tiptoe,
gilligan. I'm not asleep yet.

08:08.354 --> 08:11.889
Better hurry. That woman's gonna
be flying over at any time.

08:11.958 --> 08:14.959
- I'm doing the very best I can.
- I know you are, skipper.

08:15.028 --> 08:16.894
So stop thinkin' about
the trouble we're in.

08:16.963 --> 08:19.698
You'll never get asleep
with that on your mind.

08:24.871 --> 08:28.372
- I sure hope he gets to sleep.
- He will if he's left alone.

08:28.441 --> 08:30.174
Gilligan, I want you
to stand guard.

08:30.243 --> 08:32.610
Make sure nobody gets in there
and disturbs the skipper.

08:32.679 --> 08:34.645
- Right, nobody.
- That includes you.

08:34.714 --> 08:36.948
Especially me, I'm the worst
of the whole bunch.

08:37.017 --> 08:39.918
[Grunts]
I'm gonna go
lie down. I'm beat.

09:10.350 --> 09:11.883
Shh.

09:14.187 --> 09:17.021
No noise, gilligan.
The skipper's almost asleep.

09:17.090 --> 09:18.322
Oh!

09:18.391 --> 09:23.861
¶ When the wind blows
the cradle will rock ¶

09:23.930 --> 09:28.899
¶ when the bough breaks
the cradle will fall ¶

09:28.968 --> 09:31.970
¶ down will come baby ¶

09:32.039 --> 09:34.673
[loudly]
¶ cradle and all ¶¶

09:48.021 --> 09:51.956
(Alice mcneal on radio)
'This is Alice mcneal in the
vagabond lady saying'

09:52.025 --> 09:54.559
<i> 'aloha nui</i> to Hawaii.'

09:54.627 --> 09:57.061
'I'm planning my eta.'

09:57.130 --> 09:59.630
'this is vagabond lady
signing off.'

09:59.699 --> 10:01.666
'over and out.'

10:01.735 --> 10:03.367
signal's coming in
a lot stronger now.

10:03.436 --> 10:05.637
I've got a feeling
she's closer than we thought.

10:05.705 --> 10:08.405
Please, gilligan.
Just a little slower.

10:08.474 --> 10:09.941
Skipper.

10:10.009 --> 10:13.478
How 'bout a nice warm cup of
coconut milk to make you sleep?

10:13.546 --> 10:15.180
I've had 34 cups
of that already.

10:15.248 --> 10:19.117
I never want to see another
coconut or a lamb chop.

10:19.186 --> 10:20.251
Lamb chop?

10:20.320 --> 10:23.555
I also counted
19,000 sheep today.

10:23.623 --> 10:25.624
I've got to be alone
with my thoughts.

10:26.993 --> 10:28.126
[Sighs]

10:34.534 --> 10:35.967
That poor man
is a nervous wreck.

10:36.036 --> 10:38.202
He's all worn out
from trying to get to sleep.

10:38.271 --> 10:42.107
What he needs is something to
make him relax, calm him down.

10:42.175 --> 10:44.309
Wish we had
some tranquilizers.

10:44.377 --> 10:46.144
Yeah, tranquilizers.

10:46.213 --> 10:48.713
No, that's no good. We
don't have a prescription.

10:50.850 --> 10:52.817
Wait a minute.
Mr. howell may have some.

10:52.886 --> 10:55.119
He's always taking pills
for one thing or another.

10:55.188 --> 10:56.154
I'll go ask him.

10:56.222 --> 10:58.022
Is there something
bothering you?

10:58.091 --> 11:00.124
Yes, as a matter
of fact, there is.

11:00.193 --> 11:01.192
What is it?

11:01.261 --> 11:03.161
After we're rescued I must dash
down

11:03.229 --> 11:06.297
to Argentina to get
a new string of Polo ponies.

11:06.366 --> 11:08.533
Well, if we do return
before the matches

11:08.602 --> 11:10.368
couldn't you use
the ones we have?

11:10.437 --> 11:11.836
I suppose I could.

11:11.905 --> 11:14.739
It's just that I hate
to ride a used Polo pony.

11:14.807 --> 11:16.875
The coat is so shiny--

11:16.943 --> 11:19.877
- gilligan, hello.
- Hi, Mrs. howell, Mr. howell.

11:19.946 --> 11:21.745
Mr. howell, do you have
any tranquilizers?

11:21.814 --> 11:23.114
Of course, I do,
gilligan.

11:23.183 --> 11:24.649
Every big business man
uses tranquilizers.

11:24.717 --> 11:28.653
Makes him calm enough
to take the rest of his pills.

11:28.722 --> 11:30.188
Could I borrow some?
It's very important.

11:30.257 --> 11:32.624
Oh, yes. They're in my pill
case, they're in my shelter.

11:32.692 --> 11:35.927
You stay there, darling.
You relax. I'll go get them.

11:35.995 --> 11:37.895
There goes
a lovely lady.

11:37.964 --> 11:39.964
Gilligan, my boy,
let me tell you something.

11:40.033 --> 11:42.767
Look behind every successful man
and you will find a woman.

11:42.835 --> 11:44.102
Yes, sir.

11:44.170 --> 11:46.938
Just make sure
his wife doesn't find her.

11:49.476 --> 11:50.908
It's a marriage joke, I mean.

11:50.977 --> 11:53.744
- Oh, there we are, lovey.
- Here you are, darling.

11:53.813 --> 11:56.314
Must have been heavy. Ah..

11:58.651 --> 12:00.718
(Mr. howell)
Ah, there we are.

12:00.787 --> 12:02.353
'How did these get in here?'

12:02.422 --> 12:04.455
now, let's see, what
did I want this for?

12:04.524 --> 12:07.424
(Mr. howell)
'Oh, yes, yes. My arthritis.
Of course, arthritis.'

12:07.493 --> 12:10.895
'lovey, my pet. Do you remember
which one of my shoulders hurt''

12:10.964 --> 12:13.397
ah, no dear, you asked me
to get these for gilligan.

12:13.466 --> 12:17.035
Gilligan? Well, he seems
much too young for arthritis.

12:17.104 --> 12:19.904
No, dear. Gilligan
came in for tranquilizers.

12:19.973 --> 12:22.740
Tranquilizers. Of course,
tranq...Here they are.

12:22.809 --> 12:25.143
They would have bitten me.
Here they are, tranquilizers.

12:25.211 --> 12:27.111
- I only need a couple.
- That's perfectly alright.

12:27.180 --> 12:28.813
Take the whole.
Plenty more, plenty more.

12:28.882 --> 12:31.249
Thank you, sir.

12:31.317 --> 12:34.252
Lovey, that is the younger
generation for you.

12:34.320 --> 12:37.655
Medication for
everything and anything.

12:37.723 --> 12:38.889
Yep.

12:38.958 --> 12:40.792
What is this?

12:40.860 --> 12:44.095
"Kills pain fast,
fast, fast."

12:44.164 --> 12:45.563
Indeed.

12:45.632 --> 12:48.166
Nobody rushes a howell.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.472
[Theme music]

12:58.411 --> 13:00.511
Hi, Mary Ann. Have you
seen the professor?

13:00.579 --> 13:02.747
No, but everyone will be
showing up for dinner soon.

13:02.815 --> 13:05.282
- Is it dinner time already?
- Well, just about. Why?

13:05.351 --> 13:07.118
I borrowed these tranquilizers
from Mr. howell.

13:07.187 --> 13:09.487
I wanna put a couple in
the skipper's mango juice.

13:09.556 --> 13:11.789
That'll calm him down
and get him to sleep.

13:11.858 --> 13:13.324
What a great idea.

13:27.240 --> 13:29.540
Mary Ann, will you give
this back to Mr. howell?

13:29.609 --> 13:31.943
- I gotta go get the skipper.
- Sure.

13:48.094 --> 13:50.428
[Ginger yodeling]

13:54.167 --> 13:56.033
[Sniffs]
Hmm, what smells
so good?

13:56.102 --> 13:57.535
Burned swordfish.

13:57.604 --> 14:00.305
Burn the other side.
I think it might be better.

14:00.373 --> 14:02.407
[Yodeling]

14:06.846 --> 14:08.846
What are these for?

14:08.915 --> 14:10.715
Oh, tranquilizers.

14:10.784 --> 14:13.051
Ah, might be just
what he needs!

14:18.424 --> 14:20.524
- Come here a minute, would ya?
- Hm.

14:20.593 --> 14:23.361
Taste this thin gravy, would
you, and see what you think.

14:25.865 --> 14:29.300
O-oh! I think you need to burn
the fish a little more.

14:29.368 --> 14:30.934
(Professor)
'Hi, girls.'

14:31.003 --> 14:32.670
say, you seen gilligan?

14:32.739 --> 14:35.172
Well, he was just looking
for you. Anything wrong?

14:35.241 --> 14:37.274
No. I wanted
to see if he got the..

14:37.343 --> 14:39.210
- Got the what?
- Oh, nothing, nothing.

14:39.279 --> 14:41.479
[Sniffing]
Hey, dinner smells good.

14:56.195 --> 14:57.761
(Gilligan)
'Please, skipper.'

14:57.830 --> 15:00.998
gilligan, I don't have to eat
to keep up sta...I'm not hungry.

15:01.067 --> 15:02.500
- Please, skipper.
- Leave me alone.

15:02.568 --> 15:03.734
Sit down and take it easy.

15:03.803 --> 15:05.936
- Sit right here.
- Alright, I'll sit down.

15:06.005 --> 15:07.438
Here, skipper.
Have some mango juice.

15:07.507 --> 15:09.140
- Oh, yes.
- Thank you. Thank you.

15:09.209 --> 15:11.275
I don't want
any mango juice.

15:11.344 --> 15:13.311
How 'bout some fish.
Fish'll make you thirsty.

15:13.379 --> 15:15.145
Mary Ann, how's the fish
coming along?

15:15.214 --> 15:17.448
- Just about ready.
- Ready in just about a minute.

15:17.517 --> 15:20.017
- Here, have some mango juice.
- I don't want any juice.

15:20.086 --> 15:23.020
Please, now just leave
me alone. I wanna think.

15:23.089 --> 15:26.423
Trying to remember..

15:26.492 --> 15:27.625
[Sighs]

15:37.704 --> 15:40.871
Hey, tranquilizers. Couple of
these ought to put me to sleep.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.205
- No!
- No, skipper.

15:42.274 --> 15:44.242
I don't think you should..

15:45.678 --> 15:47.478
Here's to an early rescue.

15:54.854 --> 15:55.887
[Exhales]

15:55.955 --> 15:58.289
[Snoring]

16:06.266 --> 16:09.400
How long you thing we'd have to
wait before something happens?

16:09.469 --> 16:10.835
By the time he starts
sleep-walking

16:10.903 --> 16:13.905
that lady could go around
the world on a raft.

16:13.973 --> 16:16.007
[Snoring]

16:18.611 --> 16:19.577
[Sighs]

16:27.920 --> 16:29.320
[Mumbling]

16:30.723 --> 16:33.391
The vagabond lady.

16:33.459 --> 16:35.226
[Slurring]

16:39.332 --> 16:41.699
Get him to the beach!

16:41.768 --> 16:44.101
Skipper, skipper!

16:44.170 --> 16:47.472
Put up your arms
like you did before. Here.

17:01.854 --> 17:03.588
[Slurring]

17:06.459 --> 17:08.791
It's amazing.
It's amazing.

17:08.861 --> 17:11.094
I had no idea that four
tranquilizers could produce

17:11.163 --> 17:12.463
this much of an affect.

17:12.531 --> 17:13.564
Six.

17:13.633 --> 17:14.598
Eight.

17:14.666 --> 17:16.601
Ten.

17:18.738 --> 17:19.804
And he's out.

17:24.143 --> 17:26.777
Lovey, I told you to hurry
and get dressed. Look!

17:26.846 --> 17:28.579
We missed the cocktail hour.

17:31.784 --> 17:34.418
(Alice mcneal on radio)
'I'm happy to report
that I'm now'

17:34.487 --> 17:36.487
'one hour ahead of schedule.'

17:36.555 --> 17:38.588
yeah, go on. Go on.
What, what, what?

17:38.657 --> 17:42.125
'I'm anxious to talk to anyone
who is getting my signal.'

17:42.194 --> 17:43.860
she's not half as anxious
as we are.

17:43.929 --> 17:47.364
'Don't forget. There's
nothing but ocean under me.'

17:47.433 --> 17:50.301
'vagabond lady
signing off now.'

17:52.038 --> 17:54.071
she'll be within range of
the island pretty soon.

17:54.140 --> 17:56.774
Can we fix the transmitter
in time? That's the question.

17:56.843 --> 17:57.842
Oh, yeah.

17:57.910 --> 18:00.812
There's the answer.
Hi, skipper.

18:09.455 --> 18:11.556
- Oh!
- Shh!

18:15.595 --> 18:18.629
[Whispering]
I know where he's headed.
Back to the lagoon.

18:22.201 --> 18:24.134
- Ah!
- Shh.

18:24.203 --> 18:26.770
He mustn't be awaken. We'll
never learn what we wanna know.

18:26.839 --> 18:28.706
- But--
-<i> don't</i> utter a sound.

18:28.775 --> 18:32.276
Okay, I won't utter a sound.
But my foot's on fire. Look!

18:34.814 --> 18:36.447
[Muffled whining]

18:50.863 --> 18:53.631
Come on, let's hurry. He's
going right back to the lagoon.

18:53.700 --> 18:55.600
Just like I told you.

18:57.069 --> 19:00.104
[Groaning]

19:00.172 --> 19:01.639
Shh.

19:04.043 --> 19:05.276
Aw!

19:16.022 --> 19:18.422
[Band music]

19:24.797 --> 19:26.764
Battle stations!

19:28.167 --> 19:29.767
Yes, sir.

19:31.670 --> 19:32.870
Aye, aye, sir.

19:36.208 --> 19:37.508
[Retching]

19:39.478 --> 19:42.813
Professor, where are we?

19:42.882 --> 19:46.951
Still marooned on an island
without a transmitter.

19:47.019 --> 19:48.586
Oh, gilligan.

19:53.526 --> 19:56.727
You're reliving your landing
on guadalcanal.

19:56.795 --> 20:00.031
You're aboard your old landing
craft headed toward the beach

20:00.099 --> 20:02.200
as the battle rages.

20:05.337 --> 20:07.471
[Mimicking gunfire]

20:11.077 --> 20:12.343
[Whistling]

20:13.746 --> 20:16.147
The sea tosses your boat
around like a cork

20:16.215 --> 20:18.182
as you plow through
the crashing waves

20:18.251 --> 20:20.218
toward the distant
shoreline.

20:21.354 --> 20:23.521
[Whooshing]

20:29.195 --> 20:32.429
- Where are my seasick pills?
- I didn't bring them, dear.

20:32.498 --> 20:34.665
I had no idea we were
going out this far.

20:34.733 --> 20:37.101
I think I've
got him hypnotized.

20:37.170 --> 20:38.902
Now, everybody
remember your parts.

20:38.971 --> 20:41.538
First chance I've had to act
since we been ship wrecked

20:41.607 --> 20:44.241
and I'm playing,
gunner's mate entwistle.

20:44.310 --> 20:47.811
This is a real test for you.
You don't look a bit like him.

20:47.880 --> 20:49.713
- Thanks, gilligan.
- Alright, men.

20:49.782 --> 20:52.015
We're heading
for the beach.

20:52.084 --> 20:54.018
Battle stations,
everybody!

20:54.087 --> 20:55.118
[Trumpeting]

20:55.187 --> 20:57.121
Say out when
i call your name.

20:57.190 --> 20:59.056
Wilcowski.

20:59.125 --> 21:00.591
Here.

21:00.660 --> 21:01.959
Mcinerney!

21:02.028 --> 21:03.059
Here.

21:03.128 --> 21:04.995
- Lefkowitz!
- Oh..

21:05.064 --> 21:06.130
[Hoarse tone]
Here.

21:06.199 --> 21:08.298
What's the matter
with your voice?

21:08.367 --> 21:09.333
Laryngitis.

21:09.402 --> 21:11.535
- Here!
- Ferguson!

21:11.604 --> 21:12.736
- Here!
- 'Entwhistle!'

21:12.805 --> 21:15.172
- here!
- That's was real good, ginger.

21:15.241 --> 21:18.442
- You sounded just like him.
- We're heading in!

21:18.511 --> 21:19.844
Harris, keep
your head down.

21:19.912 --> 21:21.712
Harris is the one
with the radio manual.

21:21.780 --> 21:24.481
If anything happens to him,
somebody grab the book.

21:24.550 --> 21:26.417
Looks pretty rough up ahead!

21:26.485 --> 21:29.487
We're gonna have a hot reception
when we hit the beach.

21:29.555 --> 21:31.855
Alright, come on, folks.
Battle noises! Battle noises!

21:31.924 --> 21:34.325
[Mimicking machineguns
and planes]

21:39.565 --> 21:42.299
(Skipper)
'Testing, one, two,
three, four.'

21:42.368 --> 21:44.869
one, two, three, four.

21:47.206 --> 21:49.573
Nothing. Still
doesn't work.

21:49.642 --> 21:51.975
Are you sure you wrote those
instructions down correctly?

21:52.044 --> 21:53.511
I'm positive.

21:53.579 --> 21:56.714
Are you sure you dreamed
the instructions correctly?

21:56.782 --> 21:58.816
Well, here's no use fooling
around with this anymore.

21:58.884 --> 22:01.919
- She's probably out of range.
- Yes, I'm afraid so.

22:01.987 --> 22:04.855
Gilligan, you got sentry duty.
I'm gonna turn in for a while.

22:04.924 --> 22:07.792
- Okay, skipper.
- So am I. Goodnight.

22:07.860 --> 22:09.427
Goodnight.

22:18.770 --> 22:21.238
Testing, one, two,
three, four.

22:21.307 --> 22:24.341
Testing, one, two..

22:24.409 --> 22:26.443
[Thumping]

22:26.512 --> 22:28.245
Hello, hello,
can anybody hear me?

22:28.314 --> 22:30.881
(Female on radio)
'Nice to talk
to you, young man.'

22:30.950 --> 22:32.082
who's that?

22:32.151 --> 22:34.951
'This is Alice mcneal
in the vagabond lady.'

22:35.020 --> 22:37.721
my gosh, it's Alice!
Please stay right were you are.

22:37.790 --> 22:41.025
I got to go tell the skipper.
Now don't go away. Please.

22:43.362 --> 22:45.596
Hey, skipper!

22:45.665 --> 22:47.298
What happened?
Did you see her plane?

22:47.367 --> 22:49.866
No, no, skipper.
It's working, it's working!

22:49.935 --> 22:51.769
- What's working?
- The radio, I fixed it.

22:51.837 --> 22:53.504
I just talked to
that lady flyer.

22:53.572 --> 22:56.206
- You what?
- Honest. I'm not dreaming.

22:56.275 --> 22:59.009
I figure, you do the talking.
I don't wanna cause any trouble.

22:59.078 --> 23:00.877
I want everything
to work out just right.

23:00.946 --> 23:02.746
But how could you have
fixed the radio?

23:02.815 --> 23:05.716
It was easy. All I did
was hit it like this.

23:17.062 --> 23:20.530
Come to think of it, I guess
i dreamed the whole thing.

23:20.599 --> 23:22.499
Of course, you did.

23:22.568 --> 23:25.002
[Plane whirring]

23:27.039 --> 23:31.575
(Alice mcneal on radio)
'Nice to have talked to you
down there, whoever you are.'

23:31.644 --> 23:33.811
'we see you've been cut off.'

23:33.880 --> 23:36.714
'meanwhile, happy landing.'

23:45.457 --> 23:46.724
[bee buzzing]

23:48.227 --> 23:50.527
[Whispering]
'Shh. Skipper's
finally asleep.'

23:50.596 --> 23:52.029
quiet. Shh!

23:54.900 --> 23:56.033
[Rattling]

23:57.837 --> 23:59.036
Quiet.

24:02.374 --> 24:03.741
Shh!

24:05.544 --> 24:07.044
[Buzzing continuous]

24:18.090 --> 24:20.991
No! No, no, no, no, no.

24:24.329 --> 24:26.063
[Buzzing]

24:38.977 --> 24:40.077
Oh!

24:59.665 --> 25:01.665
¶ They're here for
a long long time ¶

25:01.734 --> 25:04.234
¶ they'll have to make
the best of things ¶

25:04.303 --> 25:05.835
¶ it's an uphill climb ¶

25:05.904 --> 25:07.938
¶ the first mate
and his skipper too ¶

25:08.007 --> 25:10.307
¶ will do their very best ¶

25:10.376 --> 25:14.611
¶ to make the others comfortable
in their tropic island nest ¶

25:14.680 --> 25:16.713
¶ no phone no lights
no motor car ¶

25:16.782 --> 25:18.815
¶ not a single luxury ¶

25:18.884 --> 25:20.884
¶ like Robinson crusoe ¶

25:20.953 --> 25:22.987
¶ it's primitive as can be ¶

25:23.055 --> 25:25.588
¶ so join us here
each week my friends ¶

25:25.657 --> 25:27.724
¶ you're sure to get a smile ¶

25:27.793 --> 25:29.927
¶ for seven stranded castaways ¶

25:29.995 --> 25:32.096
¶ here on gilligan's isle ¶¶

